%N A180783 Number of distinct solutions of Sum_{i=1..1} (x(2i-1)*x(2i)) == 1 (mod n), with x() in {1,2,...,n-1}.
%C A180783 Except for the first term, this appears to be the number of pairs of integers i,j with 1 <= i <= n, 1 <= j <= i, such that i+j == i*j (mod n), for n=1,2,3,...  - _John W. Layman_,  Oct 19 2011
%C A180783 Layman's observation holds since i+j == i*j (mod n) is equivalent to (i-1)*(j-1) == 1 (mod n). - _Max Alekseyev_, Oct 22 2011
%C A180783 For i > 1, equal to the number of elements x relatively prime to n such that x mod n >= x^(-1) mod n. - _Jeffrey Shallit_, Jun 14 2018
%C A180783 Differs from A007897 for n = 1, 35, 45 etc. - _Georg Fischer_, Sep 20 2020
